- Layout algorithms (initial version, can be refined):
  - Flowchart: simple layered graph layout (e.g., Sugiyama-style) with heuristic node spacing; start with straightforward column/row layout to meet performance goals.
  - Sequence diagrams: participants in columns, messages as horizontal arrows with vertical stacking.
  - Gantt: time axis horizontally, tasks as bars on separate rows.
  - Pie chart: compute slice angles from values and draw arcs.
  - Git graph: simple branch lanes with vertical commits.
- Integrate basic theme information (colors, font sizes) during layout where it affects geometry (e.g., text bounding boxes).
- Text measurement:
  - Risk noted in PRD: text measurement varies per backend.
  - Introduce a `TextMeasurer` trait with a default approximate implementation:
    ```rust
    pub trait TextMeasurer {
        fn measure(&self, text: &str, style: &TextStyle) -> (f32, f32);
    }

    pub struct ApproxTextMeasurer;
    ```
  - Backends may provide more accurate measurers; layout falls back to approximate when none given.
- Provide `layout(diagram: &Diagram, theme: &Theme) -> Result<Scene, LayoutError>` using default measurer.
- Ensure layout performance matches targets (50 nodes < 10ms) by avoiding excessive allocation and using simple data structures.

Pseudo-code for a simple flowchart vertical layout:
```rust
fn layout_flowchart(flow: &Flowchart, theme: &Theme) -> Scene {
    let mut elements = Vec::new();
    let node_width = 120.0;
    let node_height = 40.0;
    let v_spacing = 30.0;

    for (i, node) in flow.nodes.iter().enumerate() {
        let x = 50.0;
        let y = 50.0 + i as f32 * (node_height + v_spacing);
        elements.push(Element::Rect(Rect { x, y, width: node_width, height: node_height, style: theme.node_style(&node) }));
        elements.push(Element::Text(Text { x: x + 10.0, y: y + 20.0, content: node.label.clone(), style: theme.text_style() }));
    }

    Scene { width: 800.0, height: y_max, elements }
}
```

